[security/packetfilter/package/.*]
Description[de]=Iptables-Filterregeln, die von den installierten Softwarepaketen automatisch definiert werden und nicht modfiziert werden sollten.
Description[en]=iptables filter rules defined automatically by installed software packages. These rules should not be modified manually.
Type=str
Categories=service-security

[security/packetfilter/tcp/.*]
Description[de]=Variablen, um eigene iptables-Filterregeln zu definieren (z.B. security/packetfilter/tcp/2000/all=REJECT, security/packetfilter/udp/500/all=ACCEPT).
Description[en]=Variables to setup custom firewall rules (e.g. security/packetfilter/tcp/2000/all=REJECT, security/packetfilter/udp/500/all=ACCEPT).
Type=str
Categories=service-security

[security/packetfilter/udp/.*]
Description[de]=Variablen, um eigene iptables-Filterregeln zu definieren (z.B. security/packetfilter/tcp/2000/all=REJECT, security/packetfilter/udp/500/all=ACCEPT).
Description[en]=Variables to setup firewall rules (e.g. security/packetfilter/tcp/2000/all=REJECT, security/packetfilter/udp/500/all=ACCEPT).
Type=str
Categories=service-security

[security/packetfilter/disabled]
Description[de]=Falls diese Variable auf "true" gesetzt ist, wird die Univention Firewall deaktiviert.
Description[en]=If this variable is set to "true" the Univention Firewall is deactivated.
Type=str
Categories=service-security

[security/packetfilter/use_packages]
Description[de]=Falls diese Variable auf "false" gesetzt ist, werden die paketspezifischen Filterregel (security/packetfilter/package/...) nicht gesetzt.
Description[en]=If this variable is set to "false", all package-related filter rules (security/packetfilter/package/...) will not be set.
Type=str
Categories=service-security

[security/packetfilter/defaultpolicy]
Description[de]=Standard-Richtlinie für iptables-Filterregeln (mögliche Werte: DROP, REJECT, ACCEPT)
Description[en]=Default policy for iptables filter rules (possible values: DROP, REJECT, ACCEPT)
Type=str
Categories=service-security

